%5B%7B%22title%22%3A%22UK%20forces%20may%20be%20deployed%20to%20help%20deliver%20Gaza%20aid%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1714197614000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fichef.bbci.co.uk%2Fnews%2F1024%2Fbranded_news%2FE7E3%2Fproduction%2F_133236395_gazaaid.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.co.uk%2Fnews%2Fuk-68909511%230%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20US%20says%20no%20American%20forces%20will%20go%20ashore%20but%20an%20unnamed%20%26quot%3Bthird%20party%26quot%3B%20will%20drive%20aid%20into%20Gaza.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.co.uk%2Fnews%2Fuk-68909511%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-bbc-co-uk.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.bbc.co.uk%2Fnews%2Fuk-68909511.amp%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.co.uk%2Fnews%2Fuk-68909511.amp%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Maldives%20Doesn't%20Disclose%20Reason%20As%20Chinese%20'Spy'%20Ship%20Returns%3A%20Report%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EA%204%2C500-tonne%20high-tech%20Chinese%20'spy'%20ship%20is%20back%20in%20the%20Maldivian%20waters%2C%20two%20months%20after%20it%20spent%20a%20week%20docked%20at%20different%20ports%20in%20this%20archipelago%20nation.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EXiang%20Yang%20Hong%2003%20was%20docked%20at%20the%20Thilafushi%20industrial%20island's%20harbour%20on%20Thursday%20morning%2C%20news%20portal%20Adhadhu.com%20reported%20on%20Friday.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20%26quot%3Bthe%20government%20has%20not%20disclosed%20the%20reason%20for%20its%20return.%20But%20the%20government%20previously%20confirmed%20permission%20for%20the%20ship%20to%20dock%20before%20its%20first%20visit%2C%26quot%3B%20it%20said%2C%20days%20after%20President%20Mohamed%20Muizzu%2C%20a%20pro-China%20leader-led%20People's%20National%20Congress%20won%20the%20general%20election%2C%20securing%2066%20out%20of%20the%2093-member%20People's%20Majlis.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPresident%20Muizzu%20rode%20to%20power%20last%20year%20on%20an%20'India%20Out'%20promise%20and%20with%20a%20super%20majority%20win%20in%20parliamentary%20polls%20on%20April%2021%2C%20he%20has%20further%20consolidated%20his%20position.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20ship%20has%20now%20come%20back%20after%20skirting%20the%20Exclusive%20Economic%20Zone%20(EEZ).%20Therefore%2C%20Xiang%20Yang%20Hong%2003%20has%20been%20active%20inside%20or%20near%20Maldives%20territory%20since%20January%2C%26quot%3B%20it%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20ship%20had%20earlier%20docked%20on%20February%2023%20at%20the%20same%20Thilafushi%20port%2C%20about%207.5%20km%20to%20the%20west%20of%20Male.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20hi-tech%20ship%20reached%20Maldivian%20waters%20on%20February%2022%20after%20spending%20about%20a%20month%20near%20the%20boundary%20of%20the%20Maldives'%20EEZ.%20About%20six%20days%20later%2C%20the%20ship%20went%20back%20to%20the%20EEZ%20boundary.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20February%2C%20the%20Maldivian%20Foreign%20Ministry%20had%20said%20the%20Xiang%20Yang%20Hong%203%20was%20here%20to%20%26quot%3Bmake%20a%20port%20call%2C%20for%20the%20rotation%20of%20its%20personnel%20and%20replenishment%26quot%3B%20after%20a%20diplomatic%20request%20was%20made%20by%20the%20government%20of%20China%20to%20the%20government%20of%20Maldives.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20vessel%20would%20not%20be%20conducting%20any%20research%20while%20in%20the%20Maldivian%20waters%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20Foreign%20Ministry%20said%20on%20January%2023.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Maldives'%20proximity%20to%20India%2C%20barely%2070%20nautical%20miles%20from%20the%20island%20of%20Minicoy%20in%20Lakshadweep%20and%20300%20nautical%20miles%20from%20the%20mainland's%20western%20coast%2C%20and%20its%20location%20at%20the%20hub%20of%20commercial%20sea%20lanes%20running%20through%20the%20Indian%20Ocean%20Region%20(IOR)%20gives%20it%20significant%20strategic%20importance.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%2C%20local%20media%20reports%20in%20February%20provided%20details%20about%20the%20type%20of%20vessel%20Xiang%20Yang%20Hong%2003%3A%20The%20100-metre-long%20vessel%20was%20added%20to%20the%20fleet%20of%20China's%20State%20Oceanic%20Administration%20(SOA)%20in%202016.%20This%20is%20the%20only%204%2C500-tonne%20vessel%20currently%20in%20China.%20Since%202019%2C%20China%20has%20also%20been%20using%20the%20vessel%20to%20conduct%20'distant%20water'%20and%20'deep%20sea'%20surveys%20at%20China's%20Pilot%20Ocean%20Laboratory.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20vessel%20can%20also%20be%20used%20for%20studies%20on%20salinity%2C%20microbial%20genetic%20studies%2C%20underwater%20mineral%20exploration%2C%20and%20underwater%20life%20and%20environmental%20studies%2C%20it%20said.%20It%20has%20data%20buoys%20that%20can%20measure%20ocean%20currents%2C%20waves%2C%20and%20important%20environmental%20information.%20These%20buoys%20will%20provide%20real-time%20satellite%20information%20to%20the%20Chinese%20government%2C%20the%20report%20then%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20Friday%2C%20Adhadhu.com%20quoted%20China's%20State%20Oceanic%20Administration%20(SOA)%2C%20which%20manages%20the%20Xiang%20Yang%20Hong%2003%2C%20stating%20that%20the%20ship%20is%20the%20most%20modern%20vessel%20manufactured%20in%20the%20country%20for%20marine%20research.%20China%20says%20it%20is%20a%20comprehensive%20research%20vessel%2C%20meaning%20it%20is%20equipped%20for%20more%20than%20one%20task.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20China%2C%20the%20boat's%20endurance%20is%2015%2C000%20nautical%20miles%2C%20which%20means%20it%20could%20travel%2015%2C000%20nautical%20miles%20nonstop%20for%20its%20work%20without%20assistance.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIncidentally%2C%20the%20same%20Chinese%20vessel%20was%20present%20near%20the%20India-Maldives-Sri%20Lanka%20trilateral%20Dosti-16%20exercise%20that%20took%20place%20in%20the%20ocean%20near%20Male%20between%20February%2022%20and%2025.%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E(Except%20for%20the%20headline%2C%20this%20story%20has%20not%20been%20edited%20by%20